    <string name="guide_student_text_1">Here you will find information about the next milestone.\n\nUse the map to reach it.</string>
    <string name="guide_student_text_2">In this button you can access the contents and activities.</string>
    <string name="guide_student_text_3">Here you will see the messages your teacher has sent you.</string>
    <string name="guide_student_text_4">Do you want to know how you are doing on the route?\n\nHere you can check your progress.</string>
    <string name="guide_student_text_5">Change the color, font size, language or volume.\n\nYou will also find additional help here.</string>
    <string name="guide_student_text_6">If you have any problems, you can send an SOS message to your teacher.</string>
    <string name="guide_student_text_7">Try not to delete the application while doing the route.\n\nLeave the session when your teacher tells you to.</string>
    <string name="guide_student_title_1">Welcome!</string>
    <string name="guide_student_title_2">Contents and activities</string>
    <string name="guide_student_title_3">Messages</string>
    <string name="guide_student_title_4">My progress</string>
    <string name="guide_student_title_5">My preferences</string>
    <string name="guide_student_title_6">Send alert to my teacher!</string>
    <string name="guide_student_title_7">Leave session</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_1">This is the list of your routes.\n\nLet\'s create a route! Tap this button.\n\nTAP ANYWHERE ELSE TO SKIP THE GUIDE.\nYou can view the Guide again in "Profile".</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_10">Design a safety zone for students!\n\nYou can cover your route with circles and be notified if someone leaves this area.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_11">The geofence can be enabled or disabled, as you wish, for your next session.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_12">And that\'s it! Press back to SAVE the entire route design.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_13">With this button we can access the details of each route, configure it, edit it or delete it.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_14">The time has come!\nWith this button we create a new session for the route.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_15">Using the PIN, 6 students have joined.\nLet the session begin!</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_16">During the session, we can see if each student is online, without coverage or has left the app.\n\nWe can also notify them if they have left the geofence.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_17">Tapping on a student we can see their progress…\n\nor send them a message!</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_18">Here you can review sent messages and received alerts.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_19">Here you can send a mass message to all students.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_2">Here we write the title, level and curricular details of the route.\n\nTap the button to add the first milestone!</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_20">Here you can end the session, at any time you wish.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_21">On the Deambulario main screen you have access to the list of your sessions.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_22">Here you can access an open session, or download student answers for a closed session.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_23">Here you can configure the application, manage your account and get more help.\n\nGood luck on your routes!</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_3">We give the milestone a name and set its coordinates with this button.\n\nIn this example, the milestone will be your current location.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_4">With this button, we can add to the milestone:\n\nText, images, video or links.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_5">With this button, we add activities to the milestone:\n\nMultiple choice questions, open questions, take a photo or record a video.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_6">Press back to SAVE this milestone and return to the route.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_7">Back to the route:\n\nWe have created more example milestones.\n\nHere we can reorder the already created milestones.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_8">With this button we can access the details of each milestone, edit it or delete it.</string>
    <string name="guide_teacher_text_9">Use this button to set whether students must go through the milestones:\n\n- In the established order.\n- Freely.</string>
